commit.message: CI: test with GAP 4.13; test with mininimal set of packages loaded
Prepare includes for future GAP variants
Make sure rec(1:=2,3:=4) and rec(1:=4,2:=3) have different hashes

Don't use identity as hash func for small ints

This is a bad idea in many applications

Switch src/compiled.h to compiled.h

For better compatibility with future GAP releases
Improve printing of HashSets and HashMaps
Allow giving initial values for HashMaps and HashSets
Don't hardcode assumptions about GAP header names
Fix warnings when GAP is started with hidden implications turned off
PackageInfo.g: link to Mathjax manual by default
doc: fix some refs and other minor issues
